HEADWORD: Anthroposcopy
<hw>An`thro*pos"co*py</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`thr⟦osl⟧*p⟦ocr⟧s"k⟦osl⟧*p⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'a`nqrwpos</grk> man + <ets>-scopy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
art of discovering or judging of a man's character, passions. and
inclinations from a study of his visible features.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

